{{medical}}
{{Infobox tract|Name=弓状束|Latin=fasciculus arcuatus|Image=Arcuate fasciculus dissection and tractography.png|Caption=弓状束连接[[语言中枢|语言中枢]]的两大区域|Image2=Arcuate Fasciculus.jpg|Caption2=弓状束的纤维跟踪成像|From=[[额叶|额叶]][[布罗卡区|布罗卡区]]|To=[[颞叶|颞叶]][[韦尼克区|韦尼克区]]|System=|Function=|Location=}}'''弓状束'''（英文：Arcuate fasciculus），是连接[[大脑|大脑]][[语言中枢|语言中枢]]“[[布罗卡区|布罗卡区]]”和“[[韦尼克区|韦尼克区]]”的[[神经通路|神经通路]]，在结构上是连接[[颞叶|颞叶]]皮层尾部和[[额叶|额叶]]皮层下部的众多[[神经纤维|神经纤维]]<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=Arcuate Fasciculus|title=Encyclopedia of Child Behavior and Development|url=https://doi.org/10.1007/978-0-387-79061-9_179|publisher=Springer US|date=2011|location=Boston, MA|isbn=978-0-387-79061-9|pages=141–141|doi=10.1007/978-0-387-79061-9_179|language=en|first=Chad A.|last=Noggle|editor-first=Sam|editor-last=Goldstein}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Arcuate Fasciculus - an overview|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/neuroscience/arcuate-fasciculus|accessdate=2021-03-27|work=|publisher=Science Direct|language=en|archive-date=2022-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108173653/https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/neuroscience/arcuate-fasciculus|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 结构 ==
在结构上，弓状束属于[[大脑|大脑]][[白质|白质]]的{{le|神经径|Nerve tract}}，与{{le|上纵束|Superior longitudinal fasciculus}}平行分布。由于二者邻近，有些研究人员也将弓状束、上纵束混称<ref>{{Cite web|title=Fiber Pathways of the Brain|url=https://oxford.universitypressscholarship.com/view/10.1093/acprof:oso/9780195104233.001.0001/acprof-9780195104233-chapter-13#:~:text=The%20superior%20longitudinal%20fasciculus%20(SLF,names%20have%20been%20used%20interchangeably.&text=The%20SLF%20comprises%20three%20subcomponents,cortices%20with%20the%20frontal%20lobe.|author=Jeremy D. Schmahmann|date=2006|coauthors=Deepak N. Pandya|language=en|access-date=2021-03-27|archive-date=2022-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119073159/https://oxford.universitypressscholarship.com/view/10.1093/acprof:oso/9780195104233.001.0001/acprof-9780195104233-chapter-13#:~:text=The%20superior%20longitudinal%20fasciculus%20(SLF,names%20have%20been%20used%20interchangeably.&text=The%20SLF%20comprises%20three%20subcomponents,cortices%20with%20the%20frontal%20lobe.|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

历史上，弓状束被认为连接语言中枢“[[布罗卡区|布罗卡区]]”和“[[韦尼克区|韦尼克区]]”：布罗卡区位于[[额下回|额下回]]，韦尼克区位于后[[颞上回|颞上回]]。但如今大多数科学家认为这是个过度简化的模型<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Beyond the arcuate fasciculus: consensus and controversy in the connectional anatomy of language|url=https://doi.org/10.1093/brain/aws222|last=Dick|first=Anthony Steven|last2=Tremblay|first2=Pascale|date=2012-12-01|journal=Brain|issue=12|doi=10.1093/brain/aws222|volume=135|pages=3529–3550|issn=0006-8950}}</ref>。

== 功能 ==
一些研究人员认为“[[句法|句法]]”是人类语言的特质。尽管对于弓状束的具体功能仍有争论，主流理论认为它参与处理复杂的句法<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Syntactic processing depends on dorsal language tracts|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3201770/|last=Wilson|first=Stephen M.|last2=Galantucci|first2=Sebastiano|date=2011-10-20|journal=Neuron|issue=2|doi=10.1016/j.neuron.2011.09.014|volume=72|pages=397–403|issn=0896-6273|pmc=3201770|pmid=22017996|last3=Tartaglia|first3=Maria Carmela|last4=Rising|first4=Kindle|last5=Patterson|first5=Dianne K|last6=Henry|first6=Maya L.|last7=Ogar|first7=Jennifer M.|last8=DeLeon|first8=Jessica|last9=Miller|first9=Bruce L.|access-date=2021-03-27|archive-date=2021-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210918115213/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3201770/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有研究显示，随着弓状束的成熟、[[髓鞘|髓鞘化]]，人对于句法的处理能力随之提升。此外，弓状束损伤会导致人产生句法处理障碍。

弓状束属于双侧型结构，意味着在两侧的[[大脑半球|大脑半球]]中均存在。但是两侧的弓状束不对称：左侧的一般要强于右侧。其中左侧的弓状束被认为参与了[[句法|句法]]处理，而右侧的则被认为参与了[[韵律_(语言学)|韵律]]处理<ref name=":02">{{cite book|title=Language in our brain : the origins of a uniquely human capacity|last1=Friederici|first1=Angela|date=2017|publisher=The MIT Press|isbn=9780262036924|location=Cambridge, Massachusetts}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{cite journal|title=A qualitative and quantitative review of diffusion tensor imaging studies in reading and dyslexia|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0149763412000619|first1=Maaike|last2=Boets|first2=Bart|date=1 July 2012|journal=Neuroscience & Biobehavioral Reviews|issue=6|doi=10.1016/j.neubiorev.2012.04.002|volume=36|pages=1532–1552|issn=0149-7634|last3=Wouters|first3=Jan|last4=Ghesquière|first4=Pol|last1=Vandermosten|access-date=2021-03-27|archive-date=2019-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020213516/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0149763412000619|dead-url=no}}</ref>。进一步研究显示右侧的弓状束可能与解读人脸表情中的情绪有关<ref>{{cite journal|title=Neuropsychological evidence for the crucial role of the right arcuate fasciculus in the face-based mentalizing network: A disconnection analysis|first1=Riho|last2=Yordanova|first2=Yordanka N.|date=July 2018|journal=Neuropsychologia|doi=10.1016/j.neuropsychologia.2018.01.024|volume=115|pages=179–187|last3=Duffau|first3=Hugues|last4=Herbet|first4=Guillaume|last1=Nakajima}}</ref>。

== 临床 ==
弓状束受损可导致[[傳導性失語症|传导性失语症]]<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The role of the arcuate fasciculus in conduction aphasia|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19690094/|last=Bernal|first=Byron|last2=Ardila|first2=Alfredo|date=2009-09|journal=Brain: A Journal of Neurology|issue=Pt 9|doi=10.1093/brain/awp206|volume=132|pages=2309–2316|issn=1460-2156|pmid=19690094|access-date=2021-03-27|archive-date=2021-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210425061129/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19690094/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此外，[[口吃|口吃]]、{{le|特定型语言障碍|Specific language impairment}}、[[失讀症|失读症]]也可能与弓状束异常有关<ref>{{cite journal|title=Anomalous white matter morphology in adults who stutter|first1=M|last2=Ingham|first2=R|journal=Journal of Speech, Language, and Hearing Research|issue=2|doi=10.1044/2015_JSLHR-S-14-0193|year=2015|volume=58|pages=268–277|pmc=4675119|pmid=25635376|last3=Ingham|first3=J|last4=Grafton|first4=S|last1=Cieslak}}</ref><ref name=":22">{{cite journal|title=A qualitative and quantitative review of diffusion tensor imaging studies in reading and dyslexia|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0149763412000619|first1=Maaike|last2=Boets|first2=Bart|date=1 July 2012|journal=Neuroscience & Biobehavioral Reviews|issue=6|doi=10.1016/j.neubiorev.2012.04.002|volume=36|pages=1532–1552|issn=0149-7634|last3=Wouters|first3=Jan|last4=Ghesquière|first4=Pol|last1=Vandermosten|access-date=2021-03-27|archive-date=2019-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020213516/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0149763412000619|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

